description: {"blocks":[{"key":"emgpk","text":"Overnight liquid cultures of Agrobacterium transformed with the plasmid(s) of interest must be prepared the night before Spizellomyces transformation day. Liquid cultures must be inoculated from active plates/colonie. If you would like to use 25% glycerol stocks of previously transformed Agrobacterium, streak the desired cells onto the appropriate LB+selection plate, let it grow for 2-4 days at 28℃, then use this plate to inoculate the liquid media at least 12 hours before the intended transformation time.
